function resolveJsonPath(array $data, string $path) {
    $keys = explode('.', $path);
    $current = $data;
    
    foreach ($keys as $key) {
        if (preg_match('/(.*)\[(\d+)\]$/', $key, $matches)) {
            $current = $current[$matches[1]][$matches[2]] ?? null;
        } else {
            $current = $current[$key] ?? null;
        }
        
        if ($current === null) break;
    }
    
    if (is_array($current)) {
        return implode(', ', array_filter($current, 'is_scalar'));
    }
    
    return $current ?? '[DATA NOT FOUND]';
}

function resolveJsonPath(array $data, string $path) {
    $keys = explode('.', $path);
    $current = $data;
    
    foreach ($keys as $key) {
        if (preg_match('/(.*)\[(\d+)\]$/', $key, $matches)) {
            $current = $current[$matches[1]][$matches[2]] ?? null;
        } else {
            $current = $current[$key] ?? null;
        }
        
        if ($current === null) break;
    }
    
    if (is_array($current)) {
        return implode(', ', array_filter($current, 'is_scalar'));
    }
    
    return $current ?? '[DATA NOT FOUND]';
}

<?php
require_once './includes/config.php';
require_once './includes/function.php';

session_start();
if (!isset($_SESSION['user_id']) || !checkUserRole('document_generation')) {
    http_response_code(403);
    die('Unauthorized: Missing permissions');
}

$template_id = filter_input(INPUT_POST, 'template_id', FILTER_VALIDATE_INT);
if (!$template_id || $template_id < 1) {
    die("Invalid template ID");
}

try {
    // Validate template
    $stmt = $conn->prepare("SELECT * FROM document_templates WHERE id = ?");
    $stmt->execute([$template_id]);
    $template = $stmt->fetch(PDO::FETCH_ASSOC);
    
    if (!$template || !file_exists($template['file_path'])) {
        die("Template file not found");
    }

    // Validate Kestrel data
    if (empty($_SESSION['active_kestrel_file']) || !file_exists($_SESSION['active_kestrel_file'])) {
        die("No valid Kestrel file found");
    }
    
    // Decrypt and parse Kestrel data
    $decryptedData = base64_decode(readCustomFile($_SESSION['active_kestrel_file']));
    $kestrelData = json_decode($decryptedData, true);
    if (json_last_error() !== JSON_ERROR_NONE) {
        die("Invalid Kestrel data format: " . json_last_error_msg());
    }

    // Get mappings
    $stmt = $conn->prepare("SELECT placeholder, data_source FROM template_data_map WHERE template_id = ?");
    $stmt->execute([$template_id]);
    $mappings = $stmt->fetchAll(PDO::FETCH_KEY_PAIR);

    // Load template processor
    require_once 'vendor/autoload.php';
    $templateProcessor = new \PhpOffice\PhpWord\TemplateProcessor($template['file_path']);
    
    // Perform replacements
    foreach ($mappings as $placeholder => $jsonPath) {
        $value = resolveJsonPath($kestrelData, $jsonPath);
        
        // Verify replacement value
        if ($value === null || $value === '[DATA NOT FOUND]') {
            throw new Exception("Missing data for placeholder: $placeholder");
        }
        
        $templateProcessor->setValue($placeholder, htmlspecialchars($value, ENT_XML1 | ENT_QUOTES));
    }

    // Generate output filename
    $outputFilename = 'generated_' . basename($template['file_path']);
    $outputPath = './generated_docs/' . $outputFilename;
    
    // Ensure directory exists
    if (!is_dir('./generated_docs') && !mkdir('./generated_docs', 0755, true)) {
        throw new Exception('Failed to create output directory');
    }
    
    // Save processed document
    $templateProcessor->saveAs($outputPath);
    
    // Verify successful generation
    if (!file_exists($outputPath)) {
        throw new Exception('Document generation failed - no output file created');
    }

    // Record in history
    $stmt = $conn->prepare("INSERT INTO document_history (user_id, template_id, file_path) VALUES (?, ?, ?)");
    $stmt->execute([$_SESSION['user_id'], $template_id, $outputPath]);
    
    // Deliver file
    header('Content-Type: application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document');
    header('Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="' . $outputFilename . '"');
    readfile($outputPath);
    exit;

} catch (PDOException $e) {
    die("Database operation failed");
} catch (Exception $e) {
    die("Document generation failed: " . $e->getMessage());
}

function resolveJsonPath(array $data, string $path) {
    $keys = explode('.', $path);
    $current = $data;
    
    foreach ($keys as $key) {
        // Handle array indices
        if (preg_match('/(.*)\[(\d+)\]$/', $key, $matches)) {
            $current = $current[$matches[1]][$matches[2]] ?? null;
        } else {
            $current = $current[$key] ?? null;
        }
        
        if ($current === null) break;
    }
    
    return is_array($current) 
        ? implode(', ', array_filter($current, 'is_scalar')) 
        : ($current ?? '[DATA NOT FOUND]');
}

    die('Unauthorized: Missing permissions');
}

$template_id = filter_input(INPUT_POST, 'template_id', FILTER_VALIDATE_INT);
if (!$template_id || $template_id < 1) {
    die("Invalid template ID");
}

try {
    $stmt = $conn->prepare("SELECT * FROM document_templates WHERE id = ?");
    $stmt->execute([$template_id]);
    $template = $stmt->fetch(PDO::FETCH_ASSOC);
    
    if (!$template || !file_exists($template['file_path'])) {
        die("Template file not found");
    }

        die("No valid Kestrel file found");
    }
    
    $decryptedData = base64_decode(readCustomFile($_SESSION['active_kestrel_file']));
    $kestrelData = json_decode($decryptedData, true);
    if (json_last_error() !== JSON_ERROR_NONE) {
        die("Invalid Kestrel data format: " . json_last_error_msg());
    }

    $stmt = $conn->prepare("SELECT placeholder, data_source FROM template_data_map WHERE template_id = ?");
    $stmt->execute([$template_id]);
    $mappings = $stmt->fetchAll(PDO::FETCH_KEY_PAIR);

    require_once 'vendor/autoload.php';
    $phpWord = \PhpOffice\PhpWord\IOFactory::load($template['file_path']);
    
    // Process array iterations first
    foreach ($phpWord->getSections() as $section) {
        $elements = $section->getElements();
        foreach ($elements as $element) {
            if ($element instanceof \PhpOffice\PhpWord\Element\TextRun) {
                $text = $element->getText();
                
                // Handle array iterations
                if (preg_match('/\{\{#(\w+)\}\}(.*?)\{\{\/\1\}\}/s', $text, $matches)) {
                    $arrayData = resolveJsonPath($kestrelData, $matches[1]);
                    $replacement = '';
                    
                    if (is_array($arrayData)) {
                        foreach ($arrayData as $item) {
                            $blockContent = $matches[2];
                            preg_match_all('/\{\{(\w+)\}\}/', $blockContent, $placeholders);
                            foreach ($placeholders[1] as $placeholder) {
                                $value = resolveJsonPath($item, $placeholder) ?? '';
                                $blockContent = str_replace("{{{$placeholder}}}", $value, $blockContent);
                            }
                            $replacement .= $blockContent;
                        }
                    }
                    
                    $element->setText(str_replace($matches[0], $replacement, $text));

                    }

function processTextElement($element, $kestrelData, $mappings) {
    $text = $element->getText();
    
    // Process array blocks first
    $text = preg_replace_callback(
        '/\{\{#(\w+)\}\}(.*?)\{\{\/\1\}\}/s',
        function ($matches) use ($kestrelData) {
            $arrayPath = str_replace('_', '.', $matches[1]);
            $arrayData = resolveJsonPath($kestrelData, $arrayPath);
            $result = '';
            
            if (is_array($arrayData)) {
                foreach ($arrayData as $item) {
                    $blockContent = $matches[2];
                    $blockContent = preg_replace_callback(
                        '/\{\{(\w+)\}\}/',
                        function ($innerMatches) use ($item) {
                            $value = resolveJsonPath($item, str_replace('_', '.', $innerMatches[1])) ?? '';
                            return htmlspecialchars($value, ENT_XML1 | ENT_QUOTES, 'UTF-8');
                        },
                        $blockContent
                    );
                    $result .= $blockContent;
                }
            }
            return $result;
        },
        $text
    );
    
    // Process simple placeholders
    foreach ($mappings as $placeholder => $jsonPath) {
        $cleanPath = str_replace('_', '.', $jsonPath);
        $value = resolveJsonPath($kestrelData, $cleanPath) ?? '';
        $text = str_replace(
            "{{{$placeholder}}}", 
            htmlspecialchars($value, ENT_XML1 | ENT_QUOTES, 'UTF-8'), 
            $text
        );
    }
    
    $element->setText($text);
}

function resolveJsonPath(array $data, string $path) {
    $keys = explode('.', $path);
    $current = $data;
    
    foreach ($keys as $key) {
        if (preg_match('/(.*)\[(\d+)\]$/', $key, $matches)) {
            if (!isset($current[$matches[1]][$matches[2]])) return null;
            $current = $current[$matches[1]][$matches[2]];
        } else {
            if (!isset($current[$key])) return null;
            $current = $current[$key];
        }
    }
    
    return is_array($current) 
        ? implode(', ', array_filter($current, 'is_scalar')) 
        : $current;
}

The placeholder `{{#vehicleAssets_assets}}` should loop through each item in that array. Inside the loop, `{{vehicle_no}}` and `{{mechanical_data_engineNumber}}` should be replaced with each item's values.

Potential issues spotted:

- **JSON Path Conversion**: The code replaces underscores with dots in the JSON path. For example, `vehicleAssets_assets` becomes `vehicleAssets.assets`, which matches the sample data structure. However, if the Kestrel data uses underscores instead of dots, this might not align. But in the sample data, `vehicleAssets_assets` is under `vehicleAssets`, which has an `assets` array. So the correct path is `vehicleAssets.assets`.

- **Array Processing**: The regex for array blocks `'/\\{\\{#(\w+)\\}\\}(.*?)\\{\\{\/\1\\}\\}/s'` should match `{{#placeholder}}...{{/placeholder}}`. The `s` modifier allows `.` to match newlines, which is good. However, when processing each item in the array, the inner replacements might not be correctly accessing nested data. For example, `mechanical_data_engineNumber` is converted to `mechanical_data.engineNumber`, which should access `mechanical_data['engineNumber']` in each vehicle item.

- **Placeholder Replacement Order**: The code processes array blocks first, then simple placeholders. This is correct because array blocks might contain simple placeholders that need to be replaced after the array is processed.

- **Data Retrieval**: The `resolveJsonPath` function returns `null` if any key is missing. If a placeholder's JSON path is incorrect, it would return `null`, leading to an empty string in the replacement. This could cause placeholders to remain unchanged if the data isn't found.

<?php
require_once './includes/config.php';
require_once './includes/function.php';

// session_start(); // Uncomment if not already started in functions.php

// Validate authorization
if (!isset($_SESSION['user_id']) || !checkUserRole('document_generation')) {
    header('Content-Type: application/json');
    http_response_code(403);
    die(json_encode(['error' => 'Unauthorized: Missing permissions']));
}

try {
    // Validate template ID
    $template_id = filter_input(INPUT_POST, 'template_id', FILTER_VALIDATE_INT);
    if (!$template_id || $template_id < 1) {
        throw new Exception("Invalid template ID: $template_id", 400);
    }

    // Fetch template
    $stmt = $conn->prepare("SELECT * FROM document_templates WHERE id = ?");
    $stmt->execute([$template_id]);
    $template = $stmt->fetch(PDO::FETCH_ASSOC);
    
    if (!$template || !file_exists($template['file_path'])) {
        throw new Exception("Template file not found", 404);
    }

    // Load Kestrel data
    if (empty($_SESSION['active_kestrel_file']) || !file_exists($_SESSION['active_kestrel_file'])) {
        throw new Exception("No valid Kestrel file found", 400);
    }
    
    $decryptedData = base64_decode(readCustomFile($_SESSION['active_kestrel_file']));
    $kestrelData = json_decode($decryptedData, true);
    if (json_last_error() !== JSON_ERROR_NONE) {
        throw new Exception("Invalid Kestrel data: " . json_last_error_msg(), 400);
    }

    // Get mappings
    $stmt = $conn->prepare("SELECT placeholder, data_source FROM template_data_map WHERE template_id = ?");
    $stmt->execute([$template_id]);
    $mappings = $stmt->fetchAll(PDO::FETCH_KEY_PAIR);

    // Load template processor
    require_once 'vendor/autoload.php';
    $templateProcessor = new \PhpOffice\PhpWord\TemplateProcessor($template['file_path']);

    // Process simple placeholders
    foreach ($mappings as $placeholder => $jsonPath) {
        $value = resolveJsonPath($kestrelData, str_replace('_', '.', $jsonPath));
        $templateProcessor->setValue($placeholder, htmlspecialchars($value ?? '', ENT_XML1 | ENT_QUOTES, 'UTF-8'));
    }

    // Process array blocks
    $templateVariables = $templateProcessor->getVariables();
    foreach ($templateVariables as $varName) {
        if (strpos($varName, '#') === 0) { // Array block detection
            $cleanVar = substr($varName, 1);
            $arrayData = resolveJsonPath($kestrelData, str_replace('_', '.', $cleanVar));
            
            if (is_array($arrayData)) {
                $templateProcessor->cloneBlock($varName, 0, true, false, $arrayData);
            }
        }
    }

    // Save output
    $outputFilename = 'generated_' . bin2hex(random_bytes(8)) . '.docx';
    $outputPath = './generated_docs/' . $outputFilename;
    
    if (!is_dir('./generated_docs') && !mkdir('./generated_docs', 0755, true)) {
        throw new Exception('Failed to create output directory', 500);
    }
    
    $templateProcessor->saveAs($outputPath);

    // Record history
    $stmt = $conn->prepare("INSERT INTO document_history (user_id, template_id, file_path) VALUES (?, ?, ?)");
    $stmt->execute([$_SESSION['user_id'], $template_id, $outputPath]);

    // Deliver file
    header('Content-Type: application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document');
    header('Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="' . $outputFilename . '"');
    header('Content-Length: ' . filesize($outputPath));
    readfile($outputPath);
    exit;

} catch (Exception $e) {
    header('Content-Type: application/json');
    http_response_code($e->getCode() ?: 500);
    die(json_encode([
        'error' => $e->getMessage(),
        'code' => $e->getCode()
    ]));
}

function resolveJsonPath(array $data, string $path) {
    $keys = explode('.', $path);
    $current = $data;
    
    foreach ($keys as $key) {
        if (preg_match('/(.*)\[(\d+)\]$/', $key, $matches)) {
            if (!isset($current[$matches[1]][$matches[2]])) return null;
            $current = $current[$matches[1]][$matches[2]];
        } else {
            if (!isset($current[$key])) return null;
            $current = $current[$key];
        }
    }
    
    return is_array($current) 
        ? implode(', ', array_filter($current, 'is_scalar')) 
        : $current;
}
